22/05/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Police announced on Saturday (20 May) that they had prevented a new attempt at human trafficking near the border with Greece. 
On Thursday, officers arrested 11 Macedonian citizens for attempting to sneak Albanian citizens into Greece. 
This was the second such incident along the border in less than a week. 
In the previous case, a truck packed with 20 illegal migrants was stopped at the Bogorodica border crossing. 
(Telma TV, Makfax, A1 TV - 20/05/06)
